column5: like chewing tinfoil...  That was horrible!!

Ok, how many people kept the clip and put it in their bookmarks/favourites?
She may sound like a cat in a blender, but I hope I can still move like that (and look that healthy)  at  *cough*  76 years old.

I was truly not going to believe it could be that bad, but......... now I can't understand how anyone could listen and watch that longer than the 1m:04sec that I could bear. That was truly awful. I'm still getting shivers thinking about it as I type this.  Glad I didn't watch the whole thing.

Lots of serious thoughts this week as we commemorate Remembrance Day and think about Canadians presently in Afghanistan ......... so this might be a good time for a chuckle. This is Yoko Ono and the Plastic Ono Band performing on the Jimmy Fallon show last week. Yoko may have her strengths, but singing definitely isn't one of them. Click the link and let the horror begin:

I am not going there, unfortunately I had the misfortune of seeing her perform once and that was enough. It was my first year of University. I lived on campus just a couple of hundred yards south of Varsity Stadium and there was a great lineup at a rock concert there the first weekend after I moved in. Even my favourite artist Eric Clapton was onstage with her and John at that time but it still sounded like some one torturing a cat.  On the bright side I did get to see the Doors and a lot of other great acts of those times.  http://rockandrollrevival.tripod.com/
Im never gonna get that time back, am I???
That was her recreation of her last orgazim with John.

in the words of Meatloaf......ya took the words right out of my mouth...   holy crap ...is this somekinda new music i just dont understand????  music is supposed to make you feel something ....but ....my testicles tighting to the point of pain ????
